{"lemma":"نافِذَةٌ","slug":"نافِذَةٌ","root":"ن.ف.ذ","root_slug":"ن-ف-ذ","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ف-ذ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40210"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%90%D8%B0%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"opening in a wall, air hole"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"window","examples":[{"text":"النَّوَافِذُ مَفْتُوحَةٌ.","english":"The windows are open."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"window"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ن ف ذ (n f ḏ), verb نَفَذَ (nafaḏa, “to pierce”). An invention of the late 19th-century to mean “window” in literary Arabic. See below for dialect terms."},"ipa":["/naː.fi.ða/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40210","headword_ar":"نافذهُ","root":"nf*","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cited him before a judge."},{"kind":"text","text":"It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"An naAfa*otahumo naAfa*uwka","text_ar":"ان نَافَذْتَهُمْ نَافَذُوكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If thou cite them before a judge, they will do the same to thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If thou say to them, they will"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2823},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"say to thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"Accord. to one relation, the verb is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"q","text_ar":"ق"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"d","text_ar":"د"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) [Accord. to another, it is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*","text_ar":"ذ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}